<?php 
switch($verse){
case 1:{?>Kaf. Ha. Ya. Ain. Sad.<?php break;}
case 2:{?>A mention of the mercy of thy Lord unto His servant Zachariah.<?php break;}
case 3:{?>When he cried unto his Lord a cry in secret,<?php break;}
case 4:{?>Saying : My Lord! Lo! the bones of me wax feeble and my head is shining with grey hair, and I have never been unblest in prayer to Thee, my Lord.<?php break;}
case 5:{?>Lo! I fear my kinsfolk after me, since my wife is barren. Oh, give me from Thy presence a successor<?php break;}
case 6:{?>Who shall inherit of me and inherit ( also ) of the house of Jacob. And make him, my Lord, acceptable ( unto Thee ).<?php break;}
case 7:{?>( It was said unto him ) : O Zachariah! Lo! We bring thee tidings of a son whose name is John; We have given the same name to none before ( him ).<?php break;}
case 8:{?>He said : My Lord! How can I have a son when my wife is barren and I have reached infirm old age?<?php break;}
case 9:{?>He said : So ( it will be ). Thy Lord saith : It is easy for Me, even as I created thee before, when thou wast naught.<?php break;}
case 10:{?>He said : My Lord! Appoint for me some token. He said : Thy token is that thou, with no bodily defect, shalt not speak unto mankind three nights.<?php break;}
case 11:{?>Then he came forth unto his people from the sanctuary, and signified to them : Glorify your Lord at break of day and fall of night.<?php break;}
case 12:{?>( And it was said unto his son ) : O John! Hold the Scripture. And We gave him wisdom when a child.<?php break;}
case 13:{?>And compassion from Our presence, and purity; and he was devout,<?php break;}
case 14:{?>And dutiful toward his parents. And he was not arrogant, rebellious.<?php break;}
case 15:{?>Peace on him the day be was born, and the day he dieth and the day he shall be raised alive!<?php break;}
case 16:{?>And make mention of Mary in the Scripture, when she had withdrawn from her people to a chamber looking East,<?php break;}
case 17:{?>And had chosen seclusion from them. Then We sent unto her Our spirit and it assumed for her the likeness of a perfect man.<?php break;}
case 18:{?>She said : Lo! I seek refuge in the Beneficent One from thee, if thou art God fearing.<?php break;}
case 19:{?>He said : I am only a messenger of thy Lord, that I may bestow on thee a faultless son.<?php break;}
case 20:{?>She said : How can I have a son when no mortal hath touched me, neither have I been unchaste!<?php break;}
case 21:{?>He said : So ( it will be ). Thy Lord saith : It is easy for Me. And ( it will be ) that We may make of him a revelation for mankind and a mercy from Us, and it is a thing ordained.<?php break;}
case 22:{?>And she, conceived him, and she withdrew with him to a place.<?php break;}
case 23:{?>And the pangs of childbirth drove her unto the trunk of the palm tree. She said : Oh, would that I had died ere this and had become a thing of naught, forgotten!<?php break;}
case 24:{?>Then ( one ) cried unto her from below her, saying : Grieve not! Thy Lord hath placed a rivulet beneath thee,<?php break;}
case 25:{?>And shake the trunk of the palm tree toward thee, thou wilt cause ripe dates to fall upon thee.<?php break;}
case 26:{?>So eat and drink and be consoled. And if thou meetest any mortal, say : Lo! I have vowed a fast unto the Beneficent, and may not speak this day to any mortal.<?php break;}
case 27:{?>Then she brought him to her own folk, carrying him. They said : O Mary! Thou hast come with an amazing thing.<?php break;}
case 28:{?>Oh sister of Aaron! Thy father was not a wicked man nor was thy mother a harlot.<?php break;}
case 29:{?>Then she pointed to him. They said How can we tale to one who is in the cradle, a young boy?<?php break;}
case 30:{?>He spake : Lo! I am the slave of Allah. He hath given me the Scripture and hath appointed me a Prophet,<?php break;}
case 31:{?>And hath made me blessed wheresoever I may be, and hath enjoined upon me prayer and alms giving so long as I remain alive,<?php break;}
case 32:{?>And ( hath made me ) dutiful toward her who bore me, and hath not made me arrogant, unblest.<?php break;}
case 33:{?>Peace on me the day I was born, and the day I die, and the day I shall be raised alive!<?php break;}
case 34:{?>Such was Jesus, son of Mary : ( this is ) a statement of the truth concerning which they doubt.<?php break;}
case 35:{?>It befitteth not ( the Majesty of ) Allah that He should take unto Himself a son. Glory be to Him! When He decreeth a thing, He saith unto it only : Be! and it is.<?php break;}
case 36:{?>And lo! Allah is my Lord and your Lord. So serve Him. That is the right path.<?php break;}
case 37:{?>The sects among them differ : but woe unto the disbelievers from the meeting of an awful Day.<?php break;}
case 38:{?>See and hear them on the Day they come unto Us! Yet the evil doers are today in error manifest.<?php break;}
case 39:{?>And warn them of the Day of anguish when the case hath been decided. Now they are in a state of carelessness, and they believe not.<?php break;}
case 40:{?>Lo! We inherit the earth and all who are thereon, and unto Us they are returned.<?php break;}
case 41:{?>And make mention ( O Muhammad ) in the Scripture of Abraham. Lo! he was a saint, a Prophet.<?php break;}
case 42:{?>When he said unto his father : O my father! Why worshippest thou that which beareth not nor seeth, nor can in aught avail thee?<?php break;}
case 43:{?>O my father! Lo! there hath come unto me of knowledge that which came not unto thee. So follow me, and I will lead thee on a right path.<?php break;}
case 44:{?>O my father! Serve not the devil. Lo! the devil is a rebel unto the Beneficent.<?php break;}
case 45:{?>O my father! Lo! I fear lest a punishment from the Beneficent overtake thee so that thou become a comrade of the devil.<?php break;}
case 46:{?>He said : Rejectest thou my gods, O Abraham? If thou cease not, I shall surely stone thee. Depart from me a long while!<?php break;}
case 47:{?>He said : Peace be unto thee! I shall ask forgiveness of my Lord for thee. Lo! He was ever gracious unto me.<?php break;}
case 48:{?>I shall withdraw from you and that unto which ye pray beside Allah, and I shall pray unto my Lord. It may be that, in prayer unto my Lord, I shall not be unblest.<?php break;}
case 49:{?>So, when he had withdrawn from them and that which they were worshipping beside Allah. We gave him Isaac and Jacob. Each of them We made a Prophet.<?php break;}
case 50:{?>And We gave them of Our mercy, and assigned to them a high and true renown.<?php break;}
case 51:{?>And make mention in the Scripture of Moses. Lo! he was chosen, and he was a messenger ( of Allah ), a Prophet.<?php break;}
case 52:{?>We called him from the right slope of the Mount, and brought him nigh in communion.<?php break;}
case 53:{?>And We bestowed upon him of Our mercy his brother Aaron, a Prophet ( likewise ).<?php break;}
case 54:{?>And make mention in the Scripture of Ishmael. Lo! he was a keeper of his promise, and he was a messenger ( of Allah ) a Prophet.<?php break;}
case 55:{?>He enjoined upon his people worship and alms giving, and was acceptable in the sight of his Lord.<?php break;}
case 56:{?>And make mention in the Scripture of Idris. Lo! he was a saint, a Prophet;<?php break;}
case 57:{?>And We raised him to high station.<?php break;}
case 58:{?>These are they unto whom Allah showed favor from among the Prophets, of the seed of Adam and of those whom We carried ( in the ship ) with Noah, and of the seed of Abraham and Israel, and from among those whom We guided and chose. When the revelations of the Beneficent were recited unto them, they fell down, adoring and weeping.<?php break;}
case 59:{?>Now there hath succeeded them a later generation who have ruined worship and have followed lusts. But they will meet deception.<?php break;}
case 60:{?>Save him who shall repent and believe and do right Such will enter the Garden and they will not be wronged in aught.<?php break;}
case 61:{?>Gardens of Eden, which the Beneficent hath, promised to His slaves in the Unseen. Lo! His promise is ever sure of fulfillment.<?php break;}
case 62:{?>They hear therein no idle talk, but only Peace; and therein they have food for morn and evening.<?php break;}
case 63:{?>Such is the Garden which We cause the devout among Our bondmen to inherit.<?php break;}
case 64:{?>We ( angels ) come not down save by commandment of thy Lord. Unto Him belongeth all that is before us and all that is behind us and all that is between those two, and thy Lord was never forgetful<?php break;}
case 65:{?>Lord of the heavens and the earth and all that is between them! Therefor, worship thou Him and be thou steadfast in His service. Knowest thou one that can be named along with Him?<?php break;}
case 66:{?>And man saith : When I am dead, shall I forsooth be brought forth alive?<?php break;}
case 67:{?>Doth not man remember that We created him before, when he was naught?<?php break;}
case 68:{?>And, by thy Lord, verily We shall assemble them and the devils, then We shall bring them, crouching, around hell.<?php break;}
case 69:{?>Then We shall pluck out from every sect whichever of them was most stern in rebellion to the Beneficent.<?php break;}
case 70:{?>And surely We are best aware of those most worthy to be burned therein.<?php break;}
case 71:{?>There is not one of you but shall approach it. That is a fixed ordinance of thy Lord.<?php break;}
case 72:{?>Then We shall rescue those who kept from evil, and leave the evil doers crouching there.<?php break;}
case 73:{?>And when Our clear revelations are recited unto them those who disbelieve say Unto those who believe : Which of the two parties ( yours or ours ) is better in position, and more imposing as an army?<?php break;}
case 74:{?>How many a generation have We destroyed before them, who were more imposing in respect of gear and outward seeming!<?php break;}
case 75:{?>Say : As for him who is in error, the Beneficent will verily prolong his span of life until, when they behold that which they were promised, whether it be punishment ( in the world ), or Hour ( of Doom ), they will know who is worse in position and who is weaker as, an army.<?php break;}
case 76:{?>Allah increaseth in right guidance those who walk aright, and the good deeds which endure are better in thy Lord ' s sight for reward, and better for resort.<?php break;}
case 77:{?>Hast thou seen him who disbelieveth in Our revelations and saith : Assuredly I shall be given wealth and children!<?php break;}
case 78:{?>Hath he perused the Unseen, or hath he made a pact with the Beneficent?<?php break;}
case 79:{?>Nay, but We shall record that which he saith and prolong for him a span of torment.<?php break;}
case 80:{?>And We shall inherit from him that whereof he spake, and he will come unto Us, alone ( without his wealth and children ).<?php break;}
case 81:{?>And they have chosen ( other ) gods beside Allah that they may be a power for them.<?php break;}
case 82:{?>Nay, but they will deny their worship of them, and become opponents unto them.<?php break;}
case 83:{?>Seest thou not that We have set the devils on the disbelievers to confound them with confusion?<?php break;}
case 84:{?>So make no haste against them ( O Muhammad ). We do but number unto them a sum ( of days ).<?php break;}
case 85:{?>On the Day when We shall gather the righteous unto the Beneficent, a goodly company.<?php break;}
case 86:{?>And drive the guilty unto Hell, a weary herd,<?php break;}
case 87:{?>They will have no power of intercession, save him who hath made a covenant with his Lord<?php break;}
case 88:{?>And they say : The Beneficent hath taken unto Himself a son.<?php break;}
case 89:{?>Assuredly ye Utter a disastrous thing,<?php break;}
case 90:{?>Whereby almost the heavens are torn, and the earth is split asunder and the mountains fall in ruins,<?php break;}
case 91:{?>That ye ascribe unto the Beneficent a son,<?php break;}
case 92:{?>When it is not meet for ( the Majesty of ) the Beneficent that He should choose a son.<?php break;}
case 93:{?>There is none in the heavens and the earth but cometh unto the Beneficent as a slave.<?php break;}
case 94:{?>Verily He knoweth them and numbereth them with ( right ) numbering.<?php break;}
case 95:{?>And each one of them will come unto Him on the Day of Resurrection, alone.<?php break;}
case 96:{?>Lo! those who believe and do good works, the Beneficent will appoint for them love.<?php break;}
case 97:{?>And We make ( this Scripture ) easy in thy tongue, ( O Muhammad ) only that thou mayst bear good tidings therewith unto those who ward off ( evil ), and warn therewith the froward folk.<?php break;}
case 98:{?>And how many a generation before them have We destroyed! Canst thou ( Muhammad ) see a single man of them, or hear from them the slightest sound?<?php break;}
}?>